CUPIDON_DESCRIPTION:
By shooting his famous magic arrows, Cupid has the power to **make 2 people fall in love forever**.

On the first night (preliminary round), he designates the 2 players (or players or 1 player and 1 player) in love. Cupid may, if he wishes, designate himself as one of the two lovers.

If one of the lovers is eliminated, the other dies of grief immediately.
A Lover must never vote against his or her beloved, nor must he or she do him or her any harm (even to pretend!).
VILLAGER_DESCRIPTION:
He has no special skills.
His only weapons are the **ability to analyse** behaviours to identify werewolves, and the **strength of conviction** to prevent the execution of the innocent that he is.
WEREWOLF_DESCRIPTION:
Each night they **devour** a villager.
During the day, they try to **hide their nightly identity** to escape the popular vindictiveness.

There are 1, 2 or 3 of them, depending on the number of players.
(In no case can a Werewolf devour a Werewolf).
SEER_DESCRIPTION:
Each night, she **discovers the true personality** of a player of her choice.
She must help the other villagers, but remain discreet so as not to be discovered by the werewolves.
HUNTER_DESCRIPTION: If he is eaten by the Werewolves or unintentionally executed by the players, the Hunter **must retaliate** before he dies, by immediately eliminating any other player of his choice.
WITCH_DESCRIPTION:
She can concoct **2 extremely powerful potions**:
a potion of **healing**, to resurrect the player killed by the werewolves, a potion of **poisoning**, used at night to eliminate a player.

The Witch must use each potion **only once** in the game. She may use both potions on the **same night**.
The morning after using this power, there may be either **0 deaths**, **1 death** or **2 deaths**.

The Witch can use the potions to **her benefit**, and thus heal herself if she has just been attacked by Werewolves.
